snippet: Marginally talented and usually on the sideline, Tim Tebow somehow drew more attention than Eli Manning, whose inconsistency was worthy of weekly dissection.
abstract: Harvey Araton On Pro Football column contrasts season-long performances of New York Jets and New York Giants after both area teams fail to make it to playoffs; holds that at least Giants have only a handful of bad plays to blame, while Jets finish season as they started--in confusion bordering on chaos.
lead_paragraph: Marginally talented and usually on the sideline, Tim Tebow somehow drew more attention than Eli Manning, whose inconsistency was worthy of weekly dissection.

headline.seo: Jets and Giants: Contrasts in Failure
